Function.Name: GetKnownTradeskills
Function.Desc: Returns a table with the id numbers and names of the tradeskills known by the character

Function.Name: GetTradeskillInfo
Function.Desc: Returns a table with info about the chosen tradeskill

Function.Name: LearnTradeskill
Function.Desc: Grants the character the chosen tradeskill. If the character is already at the maximum number of tradeskills allowed, this function also drops a chosen tradeskill.

Param.Name: tradeskillId
Param.Desc: The ID number for the tradeskill that will be granted to the player

Param.Name: tradeskillIdToDrop
Param.Desc: The ID for the tradeskill that the character will drop in order to learn a new one. If the character is already at the maximum number of tradeskills learned and the tradeskill being learned is not a hobby, this value is required. If this value must be the ID of a tradeskill currently active for the character.

ReturnValue.Desc: Returns 0 if the tradeskillId is not a valid tradeskill. Otherwise, returns 1.

Function.Name: GetTradeskillTierXp
Function.Desc: Returns the amount of XP required to reach a specified tier in a tradeskill

Function.Name: GetActiveCSI
Function.Desc: Returns a table containing information on the current Client Side Interaction minigame. Returns nil if there is no Client Side Interaction taking place.

ReturnValue.Desc: A table containing information on the current Client Side Interaction.

Item.Name: type
Item.Desc: The type of Client Side Interaction being returned

Item.Name: context
Item.Desc: A string containing the text that should be displayed for the current Client Side Interaction

Item.Name: threshold
Item.Desc: The number of misses allowed for this Client Side Interaction before the user fails. This variable only exists when for Metronome CSIs

Function.Name: StartActiveCSI
Function.Desc: Starts the current Client Side Interaction

Function.Name: CancelActiveCSI
Function.Desc: Stops the current Client Side Interaction

Function.Name: IsCSIRunning
Function.Desc: Determines if a Client Side Interaction is currently running

Function.Name: CSIProcessInteraction
Function.Desc: Processes the user's input for the Client Side Interaction. Different types of Client Side Interactions behave differently

Param.Name: mouseDown
Param.Desc: Determines how to update the Client Side Interaction. For Yes/No Interactions: true indicates that the user clicked yes, false indicates no For PressAndHold: true indicates that the button was pressed down, false indicates that the button is up For RapidTapping: true indicates that the button was pressed down

Function.Name: SelectCSIOption
Function.Desc: Enters the user's input for the current Client Side Interaction. This includes final keypad entries for the Keypad interactions and the Id of the buttons pressed in Memory interactions

Param.Name: option
Param.Desc: The number that was input for the Client Side Interaction. This includes the number for keypad entries and the Id number for Memory selections

Function.Name: GetTimeRemainingForActiveCSI
Function.Desc: Returns the time remaining before the user fails the current Client Side Interaction

ReturnValue.Desc: The time remaining before the user fails, in seconds

EnumSet.Name: ClientSideInteractionType
EnumSet.Desc: An enumeration identifying the different types of Client Side Interactions

Method.Name: GetId
Method.Desc: Returns the achievement's ID number
Method.Example: function Example::GetAchievement(idSource) local tAchievements = AchievementsLib.GetAchievements() for idx = 1, #tAchievements do achCurrent = tAchievements[idx] if achCurrent:GetId() == idSource then return achCurrent end end

ReturnValue.Desc: The ID number of the Achievement

Method.Name: GetName
Method.Desc: Returns the name of the achievement
Method.Example: function Example::DisplayNames() local tAchievements = AchievementsLib.GetAchievements() for idx = 1, #tAchievements do local achCurrent = tAchievements[idx] Print(achCurrent:GetName() end

ReturnValue.Desc: The name of the achievement calling this function

Method.Name: GetDescription
Method.Desc: Returns the text for the achievement when it is completed. This function is not to be confused with Achievement:GetProgressText(), which returns the text for the achievement before it is complete
Method.Example: function Example:PrintAchievementText(achSource) if achSource:IsComplete() then Print(achSource:GetDescription()) else Print(achSource:GetProgressText()) end end

ReturnValue.Desc: The text for the completed achievement

Method.Name: GetProgressText
Method.Desc: Returns the text that the achievement shows when it is not complete. This function is not to be confused with Achievement:GetDescription(), which returns the text for the achievement when it is complete
Method.Example: function Example:PrintAchievementText(achSource) if achSource:IsComplete() then Print(achSource:GetDescription()) else Print(achSource:GetProgressText()) end end

ReturnValue.Desc: The text for the incomplete achievement

Method.Name: GetCategory
Method.Desc: Returns the name of the achievement's category
Method.Example: function Example:IsTradeskillAchievement(achSource) strCategoryName = achSource:GetCagetory() or "" if strCategoryName == "Tradeskill" or strCategoryName == "Hobby" then return true else return false end end

ReturnValue.Desc: The name of the achievement's parent category

Method.Name: GetCategoryId
Method.Desc: Returns the category Id for the Achievement's category

ReturnValue.Desc: The Id number for the Achievement's category

Method.Name: GetSubGroup
Method.Desc: Returns the name of the subgroup that the achievement belongs to

ReturnValue.Desc: The name of the subgroup that the achievement belongs to
